12 SECTION 5. IC 16-37-2-10 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
13 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 10. (a) As used in this
14 section, "DNA test" means an identification process in which the
15 unique genetic code of an individual that is carried by the individual's
16 deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) is compared with the genetic codes of
17 another individual.
18 (b) The state department may make additions to or corrections in a
19 certificate of birth on receipt of adequate documentary evidence,
20 including based on either the results of a DNA test under subsection
21 (c) or a paternity affidavit executed under section 2.1 of this chapter.
22 (c) The state department may make an addition to a birth certificate,
23 for purposes of paternity, based on the results of a DNA test only if:
24 (1) a father is not named on the birth certificate; and
25 (2) a citation to this subsection as the authority for the addition is
26 noted on the birth certificate.
27 (d) The sex designation on a birth certificate may not be
28 amended, except for either of the following:
29 (1) A medically verifiable genetic or physiological disorder of
30 sex development, including the following:
31 (A) External sex characteristics that are irresolvably
32 ambiguous.
33 (B) Forty-six (46) XX chromosomes with virilization.
34 (C) Forty-six (46) XY chromosomes with undervirilization.
35 (D) Both ovarian and testicular tissues.
36 (2) Except as provided in subsection (e), a correction of a
37 birth certificate that was previously amended to record a sex
38 other than the sex designation of the individual.
39 (e) An individual applying for a corrected birth certificate
40 under subsection (d)(2) must present a state vital record, federal
41 record, or other documentation bearing the correct sex or attesting
42 to the change.
